{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Our mission is to build"},{"time":3000,"text":"a detailed, realistic"},{"time":5000,"text":"computer model of the human brain."},{"time":7000,"text":"And we've done, in the past four years,"},{"time":10000,"text":"a proof of concept"},{"time":12000,"text":"on a small part of the rodent brain,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and with this proof of concept we are now scaling the project up"},{"time":18000,"text":"to reach the human brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"Why are we doing this?"},{"time":23000,"text":"There are three important reasons."},{"time":25000,"text":"The first is, it's essential for us to understand the human brain"},{"time":29000,"text":"if we do want to get along in society,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and I think that it is a key step in evolution."},{"time":35000,"text":"The second reason is,"},{"time":37000,"text":"we cannot keep doing animal experimentation forever,"},{"time":43000,"text":"and we have to embody all our data and all our knowledge"},{"time":47000,"text":"into a working model."},{"time":50000,"text":"It's like a Noah's Ark. It's like an archive."},{"time":54000,"text":"And the third reason is that there are two billion people on the planet"},{"time":57000,"text":"that are affected by mental disorder,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and the drugs that are used today"},{"time":63000,"text":"are largely empirical."},{"time":65000,"text":"I think that we can come up with very concrete solutions on"},{"time":68000,"text":"how to treat disorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"Now, even at this stage,"},{"time":74000,"text":"we can use the brain model"},{"time":76000,"text":"to explore some fundamental questions"},{"time":79000,"text":"about how the brain works."},{"time":81000,"text":"And here, at TED, for the first time,"},{"time":83000,"text":"I'd like to share with you how we're addressing"},{"time":85000,"text":"one theory -- there are many theories --"},{"time":88000,"text":"one theory of how the brain works."},{"time":92000,"text":"So, this theory is that the brain"},{"time":96000,"text":"creates, builds, a version of the universe,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and projects this version of the universe,"},{"time":105000,"text":"like a bubble, all around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"Now, this is of course a topic of philosophical debate for centuries."},{"time":113000,"text":"But, for the first time, we can actually address this,"},{"time":116000,"text":"with brain simulation,"},{"time":118000,"text":"and ask very systematic and rigorous questions,"},{"time":122000,"text":"whether this theory could possibly be true."},{"time":126000,"text":"The reason why the moon is huge on the horizon"},{"time":129000,"text":"is simply because our perceptual bubble"},{"time":132000,"text":"does not stretch out 380,000 kilometers."},{"time":136000,"text":"It runs out of space."},{"time":138000,"text":"And so what we do is we compare the buildings"},{"time":142000,"text":"within our perceptual bubble,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and we make a decision."},{"time":146000,"text":"We make a decision it's that big,"},{"time":148000,"text":"even though it's not that big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"And what that illustrates"},{"time":152000,"text":"is that decisions are the key things"},{"time":154000,"text":"that support our perceptual bubble. It keeps it alive."},{"time":159000,"text":"Without decisions you cannot see, you cannot think,"},{"time":161000,"text":"you cannot feel."},{"time":163000,"text":"And you may think that anesthetics work"},{"time":165000,"text":"by sending you into some deep sleep,"},{"time":168000,"text":"or by blocking your receptors so that you don't feel pain,"},{"time":171000,"text":"but in fact most anesthetics don't work that way."},{"time":174000,"text":"What they do is they introduce a noise"},{"time":177000,"text":"into the brain so that the neurons cannot understand each other."},{"time":180000,"text":"They are confused,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and you cannot make a decision."},{"time":185000,"text":"So, while you're trying to make up your mind"},{"time":188000,"text":"what the doctor, the surgeon, is doing"},{"time":190000,"text":"while he's hacking away at your body, he's long gone."},{"time":192000,"text":"He's at home having tea."},{"time":194000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"So, when you walk up to a door and you open it,"},{"time":199000,"text":"what you compulsively have to do to perceive"},{"time":202000,"text":"is to make decisions,"},{"time":204000,"text":"thousands of decisions about the size of the room,"},{"time":207000,"text":"the walls, the height, the objects in this room."},{"time":210000,"text":"99 percent of what you see"},{"time":213000,"text":"is not what comes in through the eyes."},{"time":217000,"text":"It is what you infer about that room."},{"time":221000,"text":"So I can say, with some certainty,"},{"time":225000,"text":"\"I think, therefore I am.\""},{"time":228000,"text":"But I cannot say, \"You think, therefore you are,\""},{"time":232000,"text":"because \"you\" are within my perceptual bubble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"Now, we can speculate and philosophize this,"},{"time":240000,"text":"but we don't actually have to for the next hundred years."},{"time":243000,"text":"We can ask a very concrete question."},{"time":245000,"text":"\"Can the brain build such a perception?\""},{"time":249000,"text":"Is it capable of doing it?"},{"time":251000,"text":"Does it have the substance to do it?"},{"time":253000,"text":"And that's what I'm going to describe to you today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"So, it took the universe 11 billion years to build the brain."},{"time":260000,"text":"It had to improve it a little bit."},{"time":262000,"text":"It had to add to the frontal part, so that you would have instincts,"},{"time":265000,"text":"because they had to cope on land."},{"time":268000,"text":"But the real big step was the neocortex."},{"time":272000,"text":"It's a new brain. You needed it."},{"time":274000,"text":"The mammals needed it"},{"time":276000,"text":"because they had to cope with parenthood,"},{"time":280000,"text":"social interactions,"},{"time":282000,"text":"complex cognitive functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"So, you can think of the neocortex"},{"time":287000,"text":"actually as the ultimate solution today,"},{"time":292000,"text":"of the universe as we know it."},{"time":295000,"text":"It's the pinnacle, it's the final product"},{"time":297000,"text":"that the universe has produced."},{"time":301000,"text":"It was so successful in evolution"},{"time":303000,"text":"that from mouse to man it expanded"},{"time":305000,"text":"about a thousandfold in terms of the numbers of neurons,"},{"time":308000,"text":"to produce this almost frightening"},{"time":311000,"text":"organ, structure."},{"time":314000,"text":"And it has not stopped its evolutionary path."},{"time":317000,"text":"In fact, the neocortex in the human brain"},{"time":319000,"text":"is evolving at an enormous speed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"If you zoom into the surface of the neocortex,"},{"time":324000,"text":"you discover that it's made up of little modules,"},{"time":327000,"text":"G5 processors, like in a computer."},{"time":329000,"text":"But there are about a million of them."},{"time":332000,"text":"They were so successful in evolution"},{"time":334000,"text":"that what we did was to duplicate them"},{"time":336000,"text":"over and over and add more and more of them to the brain"},{"time":338000,"text":"until we ran out of space in the skull."},{"time":341000,"text":"And the brain started to fold in on itself,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and that's why the neocortex is so highly convoluted."},{"time":346000,"text":"We're just packing in columns,"},{"time":348000,"text":"so that we'd have more neocortical columns"},{"time":351000,"text":"to perform more complex functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354000,"text":"So you can think of the neocortex actually as"},{"time":356000,"text":"a massive grand piano,"},{"time":358000,"text":"a million-key grand piano."},{"time":361000,"text":"Each of these neocortical columns"},{"time":363000,"text":"would produce a note."},{"time":365000,"text":"You stimulate it; it produces a symphony."},{"time":368000,"text":"But it's not just a symphony of perception."},{"time":371000,"text":"It's a symphony of your universe, your reality."},{"time":374000,"text":"Now, of course it takes years to learn how"},{"time":377000,"text":"to master a grand piano with a million keys."},{"time":380000,"text":"That's why you have to send your kids to good schools,"},{"time":382000,"text":"hopefully eventually to Oxford."},{"time":384000,"text":"But it's not only education."},{"time":387000,"text":"It's also genetics."},{"time":389000,"text":"You may be born lucky,"},{"time":391000,"text":"where you know how to master your neocortical column,"},{"time":395000,"text":"and you can play a fantastic symphony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"In fact, there is a new theory of autism"},{"time":400000,"text":"called the \"intense world\" theory,"},{"time":402000,"text":"which suggests that the neocortical columns are super-columns."},{"time":406000,"text":"They are highly reactive, and they are super-plastic,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and so the autists are probably capable of"},{"time":413000,"text":"building and learning a symphony"},{"time":415000,"text":"which is unthinkable for us."},{"time":417000,"text":"But you can also understand"},{"time":419000,"text":"that if you have a disease"},{"time":421000,"text":"within one of these columns,"},{"time":423000,"text":"the note is going to be off."},{"time":425000,"text":"The perception, the symphony that you create"},{"time":427000,"text":"is going to be corrupted,"},{"time":429000,"text":"and you will have symptoms of disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"So, the Holy Grail for neuroscience"},{"time":436000,"text":"is really to understand the design of the neocoritical column --"},{"time":440000,"text":"and it's not just for neuroscience;"},{"time":442000,"text":"it's perhaps to understand perception, to understand reality,"},{"time":445000,"text":"and perhaps to even also understand physical reality."},{"time":449000,"text":"So, what we did was, for the past 15 years,"},{"time":452000,"text":"was to dissect out the neocortex, systematically."},{"time":456000,"text":"It's a bit like going and cataloging a piece of the rainforest."},{"time":460000,"text":"How many trees does it have?"},{"time":462000,"text":"What shapes are the trees?"},{"time":464000,"text":"How many of each type of tree do you have? Where are they positioned?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"But it's a bit more than cataloging because you actually have to"},{"time":469000,"text":"describe and discover all the rules of communication,"},{"time":473000,"text":"the rules of connectivity,"},{"time":475000,"text":"because the neurons don't just like to connect with any neuron."},{"time":478000,"text":"They choose very carefully who they connect with."},{"time":481000,"text":"It's also more than cataloging"},{"time":484000,"text":"because you actually have to build three-dimensional"},{"time":486000,"text":"digital models of them."},{"time":488000,"text":"And we did that for tens of thousands of neurons,"},{"time":490000,"text":"built digital models of all the different types"},{"time":493000,"text":"of neurons we came across."},{"time":495000,"text":"And once you have that, you can actually"},{"time":497000,"text":"begin to build the neocortical column."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501000,"text":"And here we're coiling them up."},{"time":504000,"text":"But as you do this, what you see"},{"time":507000,"text":"is that the branches intersect"},{"time":509000,"text":"actually in millions of locations,"},{"time":512000,"text":"and at each of these intersections"},{"time":515000,"text":"they can form a synapse."},{"time":517000,"text":"And a synapse is a chemical location"},{"time":519000,"text":"where they communicate with each other."},{"time":522000,"text":"And these synapses together"},{"time":524000,"text":"form the network"},{"time":526000,"text":"or the circuit of the brain."},{"time":529000,"text":"Now, the circuit, you could also think of as"},{"time":533000,"text":"the fabric of the brain."},{"time":535000,"text":"And when you think of the fabric of the brain,"},{"time":538000,"text":"the structure, how is it built? What is the pattern of the carpet?"},{"time":542000,"text":"You realize that this poses"},{"time":544000,"text":"a fundamental challenge to any theory of the brain,"},{"time":548000,"text":"and especially to a theory that says"},{"time":550000,"text":"that there is some reality that emerges"},{"time":552000,"text":"out of this carpet, out of this particular carpet"},{"time":555000,"text":"with a particular pattern."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"The reason is because the most important design secret of the brain"},{"time":560000,"text":"is diversity."},{"time":562000,"text":"Every neuron is different."},{"time":564000,"text":"It's the same in the forest. Every pine tree is different."},{"time":566000,"text":"You may have many different types of trees,"},{"time":568000,"text":"but every pine tree is different. And in the brain it's the same."},{"time":571000,"text":"So there is no neuron in my brain that is the same as another,"},{"time":574000,"text":"and there is no neuron in my brain that is the same as in yours."},{"time":577000,"text":"And your neurons are not going to be oriented and positioned"},{"time":580000,"text":"in exactly the same way."},{"time":582000,"text":"And you may have more or less neurons."},{"time":584000,"text":"So it's very unlikely"},{"time":586000,"text":"that you got the same fabric, the same circuitry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"So, how could we possibly create a reality"},{"time":592000,"text":"that we can even understand each other?"},{"time":595000,"text":"Well, we don't have to speculate."},{"time":597000,"text":"We can look at all 10 million synapses now."},{"time":600000,"text":"We can look at the fabric. And we can change neurons."},{"time":603000,"text":"We can use different neurons with different variations."},{"time":605000,"text":"We can position them in different places,"},{"time":607000,"text":"orient them in different places."},{"time":609000,"text":"We can use less or more of them."},{"time":611000,"text":"And when we do that"},{"time":613000,"text":"what we discovered is that the circuitry does change."},{"time":616000,"text":"But the pattern of how the circuitry is designed does not."},{"time":623000,"text":"So, the fabric of the brain,"},{"time":625000,"text":"even though your brain may be smaller, bigger,"},{"time":627000,"text":"it may have different types of neurons,"},{"time":630000,"text":"different morphologies of neurons,"},{"time":632000,"text":"we actually do share"},{"time":635000,"text":"the same fabric."},{"time":637000,"text":"And we think this is species-specific,"},{"time":639000,"text":"which means that that could explain"},{"time":641000,"text":"why we can't communicate across species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"So, let's switch it on. But to do it, what you have to do"},{"time":646000,"text":"is you have to make this come alive."},{"time":648000,"text":"We make it come alive"},{"time":650000,"text":"with equations, a lot of mathematics."},{"time":652000,"text":"And, in fact, the equations that make neurons into electrical generators"},{"time":656000,"text":"were discovered by two Cambridge Nobel Laureates."},{"time":659000,"text":"So, we have the mathematics to make neurons come alive."},{"time":662000,"text":"We also have the mathematics to describe"},{"time":664000,"text":"how neurons collect information,"},{"time":667000,"text":"and how they create a little lightning bolt"},{"time":670000,"text":"to communicate with each other."},{"time":672000,"text":"And when they get to the synapse,"},{"time":674000,"text":"what they do is they effectively,"},{"time":676000,"text":"literally, shock the synapse."},{"time":679000,"text":"It's like electrical shock"},{"time":681000,"text":"that releases the chemicals from these synapses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"And we've got the mathematics to describe this process."},{"time":687000,"text":"So we can describe the communication between the neurons."},{"time":691000,"text":"There literally are only a handful"},{"time":694000,"text":"of equations that you need to simulate"},{"time":696000,"text":"the activity of the neocortex."},{"time":698000,"text":"But what you do need is a very big computer."},{"time":701000,"text":"And in fact you need one laptop"},{"time":703000,"text":"to do all the calculations just for one neuron."},{"time":706000,"text":"So you need 10,000 laptops."},{"time":708000,"text":"So where do you go? You go to IBM,"},{"time":710000,"text":"and you get a supercomputer, because they know how to take"},{"time":712000,"text":"10,000 laptops and put it into the size of a refrigerator."},{"time":716000,"text":"So now we have this Blue Gene supercomputer."},{"time":719000,"text":"We can load up all the neurons,"},{"time":721000,"text":"each one on to its processor,"},{"time":723000,"text":"and fire it up, and see what happens."},{"time":727000,"text":"Take the magic carpet for a ride."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"Here we activate it. And this gives the first glimpse"},{"time":733000,"text":"of what is happening in your brain"},{"time":735000,"text":"when there is a stimulation."},{"time":737000,"text":"It's the first view."},{"time":739000,"text":"Now, when you look at that the first time, you think,"},{"time":741000,"text":"\"My god. How is reality coming out of that?\""},{"time":746000,"text":"But, in fact, you can start,"},{"time":749000,"text":"even though we haven't trained this neocortical column"},{"time":753000,"text":"to create a specific reality."},{"time":755000,"text":"But we can ask, \"Where is the rose?\""},{"time":759000,"text":"We can ask, \"Where is it inside,"},{"time":761000,"text":"if we stimulate it with a picture?\""},{"time":764000,"text":"Where is it inside the neocortex?"},{"time":766000,"text":"Ultimately it's got to be there if we stimulated it with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"So, the way that we can look at that"},{"time":772000,"text":"is to ignore the neurons, ignore the synapses,"},{"time":775000,"text":"and look just at the raw electrical activity."},{"time":777000,"text":"Because that is what it's creating."},{"time":779000,"text":"It's creating electrical patterns."},{"time":781000,"text":"So when we did this,"},{"time":783000,"text":"we indeed, for the first time,"},{"time":785000,"text":"saw these ghost-like structures:"},{"time":788000,"text":"electrical objects appearing"},{"time":791000,"text":"within the neocortical column."},{"time":794000,"text":"And it's these electrical objects"},{"time":797000,"text":"that are holding all the information about"},{"time":800000,"text":"whatever stimulated it."},{"time":803000,"text":"And then when we zoomed into this,"},{"time":805000,"text":"it's like a veritable universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"So the next step"},{"time":811000,"text":"is just to take these brain coordinates"},{"time":815000,"text":"and to project them into perceptual space."},{"time":819000,"text":"And if you do that,"},{"time":821000,"text":"you will be able to step inside"},{"time":823000,"text":"the reality that is created"},{"time":825000,"text":"by this machine,"},{"time":827000,"text":"by this piece of the brain."},{"time":830000,"text":"So, in summary,"},{"time":832000,"text":"I think that the universe may have --"},{"time":834000,"text":"it's possible --"},{"time":836000,"text":"evolved a brain to see itself,"},{"time":839000,"text":"which may be a first step in becoming aware of itself."},{"time":844000,"text":"There is a lot more to do to test these theories,"},{"time":846000,"text":"and to test any other theories."},{"time":849000,"text":"But I hope that you are at least partly convinced"},{"time":852000,"text":"that it is not impossible to build a brain."},{"time":855000,"text":"We can do it within 10 years,"},{"time":857000,"text":"and if we do succeed,"},{"time":859000,"text":"we will send to TED, in 10 years,"},{"time":861000,"text":"a hologram to talk to you. Thank you."},{"time":864000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}